Experts in America found that 50 per cent of pensioners with investments panicked and sold them after the stock market fell by 30 per cent .
If they had resisted temptation to sell, the same pot would be worth £141,000 today .
Those who sold at the lowest point eight years ago with a pension of £100,000 would only have £63,000 .
It comes just days before retirees in Britain are given power to decide how to spend their life savings for the first time ever .